author: bergmeister
body:
The cmdlet help link for `New-TemporaryFile` is broken.

Steps to reproduce
------------------

```powershell
Get-Help New-TemporaryFile -Online
```

Expected behavior
-----------------

I get redirected to a help page like e.g. to
https://docs.microsoft.com/powershell/module/Microsoft.PowerShell.Utility/New-TemporaryFile?view=powershell-6.0

Actual behavior
---------------

I get redirected to
https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc732148.aspx
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9250262/36355051-0736f7ba-14d5-11e8-89e7-541febedff10.png)


Environment data
----------------

<!-- provide the output of $PSVersionTable -->

```powershell
> $PSVersionTable
Name                           Value
----                           -----
PSVersion                      6.1.0-preview.582
PSEdition                      Core
GitCommitId                    v6.1.0-preview.582
OS                             Microsoft Windows 10.0.16299
Platform                       Win32NT
PSCompatibleVersions           {1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0...}
PSRemotingProtocolVersion      2.3
SerializationVersion           1.1.0.1
WSManStackVersion              3.0
```
title: Cmdlet Help link broken for New-TemporaryFile
